Classical swine fever, Mongolia
---------------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 7 Jul 2014 from Dr Bolortuya Purevsuren, Deputy Director and Chief Veterinary Officer, Veterinary and Animal Breeding Agency, Ministry for Industry and Agriculture, Ulaanbaatar, Mongolia

Summary:
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 26 Jun 2014
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 5 Jul 2014
Report date: 7 Jul 2014
Reason for notification: 1st occurrence of a listed disease
Manifestation of disease: Clinical disease
Causal agent: Classical swine fever virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks: Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1: Daagan tolgoi "New crop" company, 21th khoroo, Songinikharikhan district, Tov
Date of start of the outbreak: 26 Jun 2014
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 993 / 451 / - / 993 / 0

Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 45.42 percent / ** / ** / **
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter
**Not calculated because of missing information

Epidemiology:
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive

Control measures
Measures applied: stamping out; quarantine; movement control inside the country; disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s); no treatment of affected animals

Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total vaccinated / Details
Tov / Swine / 330

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results:
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
State Central Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / antigen (Ag) detection ELISA / 5 Jul 2014 / Positive
State Central Veterinary Laboratory (National laboratory) / Swine / reverse transcription-polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 5 Jul 2014 / Positive

Future Reporting:
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.

